<page_title>A workaround for aligning an image with a component </page_title>
<text> A workaround for aligning an image with a component

There is currently a bug related to inserting an image to a location to the left or right of a model container. The bug causes an unwanted vertical lift of the image from the baseline of the model container, as is illustrated in the following:

  

(a) The vertical shift of the image caused by a Java bug.

The workaround to this problem is to insert a text box and place the image inside the text box using just a HTML tag &lt;img src=&quot;file name of the image&quot;&gt; in the text box&apos;s HTML body. This solves the problem, as is shown below:

  

(b) The correct alignment of an image with a model container.


&lt;Index of tips&gt;


</text>
